@node "What's new" "What's new"
@next "Requirements"
@prev "Introduction"
 Changes (since MTX v1.4)

- small bugfixes - easier installation - "fix pointer" option in the CGX
version - tooltypes support - "show settings" option

Changes (since MTX v1.3)

- from now on MTX is a commodity - new font sets - four display modes - port 2
is checked too


Changes (since MTX v1.2)

- now the mouse pointer is blanked too. (AGA&CGX) - lock/unlock screen
function has been added. (CGX) - the last line wasn't drawn correctly.
(AGA&CGX) - now the background can be also black. (AGA&CGX) - you can create
your own set of fonts. (AGA&CGX) - the bug which might crash your computer
  (findport() without forbid) has been fixed. (AGA&CGX)
@endnode

