System requirements:

-Amiga OS 3.x
-68020+
-CyberGraphX or AGA

-gadtools.library v39+
-reqtools.library  

@endnode

@node "Installation" "Installation"
@next "Usage"
@prev "Requirements"
@smartwrap
Installation.

It's very simple !  Just move correct version (AGA/CGX) of "MTX" and
"MTX.info", to your WBStartup dir.

@endnode

@node "Usage" "Usage"
@next "FAQ"
@prev "Installation"
 MTX can be controlled by two ways:  by prefs interface and by icon
tooltypes.

MTX is a commodity, so the interface can be enabled by running Exchange and
clicking on 'Show interface' button.  You can also make interface visible
on startup by setting CX_POPUP to 'YES'.

Available tooltypes: 

DONOTWAIT 			- run immediately 
CX_POPUP (YES/NO)		- show/hide prefs window at startup
PRIORITY (value)		- MTX priority
TIME 	(seconds)		- activation time
SPEED 	(0-9)			- the speed of Matrix
RANDOM	(0-9) 			- higher value = more chars appear at once
BRIGHT	(0-16)			- brightness of the Matrix

FONT				- six different font sets
(Old/Old2/New/Big/Big2/Huge)	

DISPLAY				- screen size
(640x480/800x600/1024x768) 	

FIXPOINTER (YES/NO) 		- enable if your pointer gets corrupted
				after blank

All the functions are also available from gui:
Speed, Random, Time, Bright, Fonts, Display, Priority, Fix Pointer.

'Hide Settings'	checkmark acts like CX_POPUP tooltype.

'Display' cycle gadget has two more options:

Custom 		- you can choose screen mode simply by clicking on 'Screenmode'
		  button (requester will pop up))
Use WB 		- creates Workbench screen clone for MTX

@endnode

@node "FAQ" "FAQ"
@next "Author"
@prev "Usage"
@smartwrap
Q:Why the fonts are linked with the executable?

A:When v1.2 came out, some people wanted to make another font sets, they
wanted to load fonts from external file. v1.3 had this feature, but noone have
done anything. Anyway some people noticed that they do not like mess in c:
directory.

Q:Does AGA version differs from CGX one?

A:Yes, AGA version has only 3 fontsets. You can switch screen mode either to
640x512 or any in "Use WB" mode. This actually is a bit slower, so you're
suggested to do not use it if you have 640x512 Workbench.

If you have huge WB (eg.SuperHires Laced) then you might notice slowdown due
to low AGA data bandwith, but you can fix it a bit with setting "Random" value
to 2 or even 1. You may also be quite astonished that your 040 is not enough
:). Well AGA is quite slow in high resolutions.

@endnode

